<div id="review_384993376" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/384993376" />
    <a title="Betsy" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/11601518-betsy"><img alt="Betsy" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/f_50x66-6a03a5c12233c941481992b82eea8d23.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/384993376?book_show_action=true">Aug 05, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Betsy" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Betsy" href="/user/show/11601518-betsy">Betsy</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>


          <div><span class="uitext greyText">Recommends it for: </span>
           <span class="uitext reviewText">Everyone</span></div>

          <div>
    <span class="greyText">Recommended to Betsy by: </span>
      Personal friends
  </div>


    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer384993376" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4214031181667437684">Let me begin by not burying the lead: if you&apos;re seriously interested in experiencing a higher quality and more satisfying life experience, don&apos;t just read this book - put it to work in your life!<br/><br/>I picked this book up at the insistence of a friend using it to help her redefine her life during a particularly difficult time. Based on her excitement and personal experience, I read it more out of curiosity and skepticism than anything else. I&apos;m not into self-help books and hesitate to classify this a</span>
  <span id="freeText4214031181667437684" style="display:none">Let me begin by not burying the lead: if you're seriously interested in experiencing a higher quality and more satisfying life experience, don't just read this book - put it to work in your life!<br /><br />I picked this book up at the insistence of a friend using it to help her redefine her life during a particularly difficult time. Based on her excitement and personal experience, I read it more out of curiosity and skepticism than anything else. I'm not into self-help books and hesitate to classify this as such. It's more of an interactive course in living. To make a long story short, I wish I had this book twenty years ago - it is that good!<br /><br />As the subtitle states, this book is about how truly happy people are different and what we can learn from them. Ian draws on a diverse and interesting set of examples and personal anecdotes as he delivers a compelling illustration of the ingredients that drive wonderful lives based on decades of research. The first part explores life and the things that influence it and define its experience. Ian then transitions into features the happiest people share with each other. By the end, you're putting one and one together and exploring your life in new ways and learning how to improve its experience.<br /><br />It's worth mentioning that this book doesn't contain the typical fluff and rhetoric found in most self-help books. It's a smart, well written, easy, and addicting read. Breck obviously makes an effort to make everything understandable and accessible to the reader instead of flaunting his deep knowledge. I appreciated that. Surprisingly, once you start answering questions and experiencing this book within the context of your own life, it takes on an entirely different and brilliant form. This book is designed to be experienced, and it's perfect for groups. I often find myself and friends talking about ideas this book presents for hours on end.<br /><br />If you want to design and experience a higher quality life for yourself with insight from the smartest guy in the room, spend some quality time with Ian Breck. You won't be disappointed.<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="4214031181667437684" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


